casebody.data:
Julio C. MARRERO and Kathleen Marrero, Appellant(s)/Petitioner(s),
v.
Orlando BENITEZ, Jr., Appellee(s)/Respondent(s), CASE NO.: 3D17-1814 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. OCTOBER 13, 2017 SUAREZ, LOGUE and LINDSEY, JJ., concur.

ORDERED that appellants' voluntary notice of dismissal of appeal is recognized by the Court, and this appeal from the Circuit Court for Miami-Dade County, Florida is hereby dismissed.

Appellee's motion to dismiss appeal for lack of appellate jurisdiction is hereby denied as moot.

Upon consideration of appellee's motion for attorney's fees, it is ordered that said motion is granted and remanded to the trial court to fix amount.
